Zackary, who has Treacher Collins syndrome, had the opportunity of a lifetime to spend three days with his hero - a one of the world's most recognised individual who suffers from the same genetic disorder.

Mother Sarah Walton, who contacted Mr Lancaster and asked him to spend time with her son during his nation-wide tour to educate schools about Treacher Collins syndrome, says the 30-year-old of West Yorkshire has left a huge impact on her family.

